RAWALPINDI, Jul 29 (APP):Three innocent civilians were injured on Wednesday as Indian Army troops resorted to unprovoked ceasefire violation (CFV) deliberately targeting the civilian population in Rakhchikri Sector along the Line of Control (LoC).
According to Inter Services Public Relations (ISPR), the injured, residents of Akhori village, included two women. The Pakistan Army troops effectively responded to the Indian firing.
